name: 15795 Bridger Canyon Rd, Bozeman, MT 59715, USA
East Clinton Branch Library
directions: Two individual room bathrooms, must have a colored/numbered key to get in. Yellow door 1 is the first door on the left down hallway, Green door 2 is the third door. Keys are hanging near staff desk by the newspapers. Our doors are tricky: you must put the corresponding key into the black/silver box next to the door instead of the actual door lock. Turn it to the right as far as you can and the door will slowly open, bring the key inside with you. It is an automatic door so it will take quite a few seconds to close behind you. To exit the bathroom, push the blue handicap button on the wall, then hang the key back up or give to a staff member.
comment: Free for all to use during open hours of the library.

If someone does tell you to buy something, there’s usually like cheap bottled water (or you can explain your situation). It’s even marked “LGBTQ friendly” on google maps, and there’s lots of parking & nice places to sit!

name: Dandy Lion Cuts for Kids
directions: We are an open concept salon that is open by appointment. The single room, handicapped accessible restroom is located toward the back end of the space. There is access to free use of the changing table, wipes, diaper genie, and sanitary products.
comment: As you enter the space a stylist should greet you with “hello!” Or “how can we help you?”. If you aren’t comfortable stating out loud that you need the restroom just give us the ASL bathroom sign (a fist with your thumb between your middle and pointer fingers and shake it a bit) and you will be pointed in the right direction.

comment: Thalia Hall is a live music venue.
